<subSubSection id="C3136ACE732BFFA19014FEA5F790FDDD" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB63945732BFFA19014FEA5F790FDDD" blockId="6.[191,1441,324,551]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19014FEA5F718FE85" bold="true" box="[256,367,357,383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844B4732BFFA19062FEA5F476FE85" author="Bates HW" box="[374,513,357,383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="143 - 183" refId="ref14059" refString="Bates HW. 1892. Additions to the Longicornia of Mexico and Central America, with remarks on some of the previously recorded species. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1892: 143 - 183." type="journal article" year="1892">Bates (1892)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C6732BFFA1936AFEA5F567FE85" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1892" box="[638,784,357,383]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anatinomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA1936AFEA5F567FE85" box="[638,784,357,383]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Anatinomma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include his new species 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C6732BFFA19550FEA5F2AAFE84" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1892" box="[1092,1245,356,383]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anatinomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alveolatum">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19550FEA5F2AAFE84" box="[1092,1245,356,383]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">A. alveolatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The second part of the generic name, the Greek word “ 
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19365FE44F4CEFE5A" bold="true" box="[625,697,388,416]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">ὄμμᾰ”</emphasis>
(ómma), means “eyes.” According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844B4732BFFA19576FE46F29AFE5A" author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1122,1261,390,416]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref14721" refString="ICZN (International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature). 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature; London. xxx + 306 p." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 30.1.2), “a genus-group name that is or ends in a Greek word transliterated into Latin without other changes, takes the gender given for that word in standard Greek dictionaries.” As “ómma” is neuter gender, two species-group names need to be corrected: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C6732BFFA190A2FE2BF4A9FDFF" authority="Fisher, 1944" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1944" box="[438,734,491,517]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anatinomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA190A2FE2BF7BFFDFF" box="[438,456,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA190C1FE2BF43AFDFF" box="[469,589,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">brevicornis</emphasis>
Fisher, 1944
</taxonomicName>
, becomes 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C6732BFFA19247FE2BF591FDFF" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1944" box="[851,998,491,517]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anatinomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicorne">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19247FE2BF512FDFF" box="[851,869,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19267FE2BF591FDFF" box="[883,998,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">brevicorne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C6732BFFA19531FE2BF68EFDDC" authority="Chemsak and Linsley, 1964" authorityName="Chemsak and Linsley" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anatinomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19531FE2BF240FDFF" box="[1061,1079,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA19551FE2BF2D4FDFF" box="[1093,1187,491,517]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">insularis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844B4732BFFA195BEFE2BF68EFDDC" author="Chemsak JA &amp; Linsley EG" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="216 - 226" refId="ref14348" refString="Chemsak JA, Linsley EG. 1964. Descriptions and records of Hesperophanini, with keys to the species of Anatinomma and Amphelictus (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 37 (3): 216 - 226." type="journal article" year="1964">Chemsak and Linsley, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, becomes 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942C6732BFFA1907EFDCDF796FDDC" authorityName="Chemsak and Linsley" authorityYear="1964" box="[362,481,524,551]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anatinomma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insulare">
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA1907EFDCDF70AFDDD" box="[362,381,525,551]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97DE557732BFFA1909EFDCCF796FDDC" box="[394,481,524,550]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">insulare</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
